A '''dependent United States visa''' is a type of [[Visa (document)|visa]] which allows spouses and children to travel to the [[United States]] for the purpose of accompanying a family member with a corresponding visa type. While many visa classes have their own dependent visa, others do not. Some of these require all family members to apply for the same visa class, such as [[E-2 visa|E-2]] and [[C-2 visa|C-2]] visas. Others such as the [[D-1 visa]] do not allow travel for dependents at all.<ref name=pocket/> Certain restrictions apply depending on the type of dependent visa an individual is seeking.

The dependent visa classes are as follows:

* [[CW-2 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted on a [[CW-1 visa]]. Children must be under 18 years of age.<ref name=pocket>{{cite book |last= |first= |date=2013 |title=Immigration pocket field guide|url= |location= |publisher=Matthew Bender & Company, Inc|page= |isbn=}}</ref>{{rp|20}}
* [[E-3D visa]] - for dependents of those admitted on an [[E-3 visa]]. Spouses may apply for authorization to work while in the US.<ref name="pocket"/>
* [[F-2 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted on an [[F-1 visa]]. Employment is not authorized. Children may attend primary and secondary school.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uscis.gov/working-united-states/students-and-exchange-visitors |title=Students and Exchange Visitors |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=US Citizenship and Immigration Services |publisher= |access-date=13 October 2016 |quote=}}</ref>
* [[H-4 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted under another [[H visa (disambiguation)|H visa]] <!-- This link to a disambiguation page is intentional. -->{{cite web |url=https://www.uscis.gov/working-united-states/temporary-workers/employment-authorization-certain-h-4-dependent-spouses |title=Employment Authorization for Certain H-4 Dependent Spouses |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=USCIS |publisher= |access-date=13 October 2016 |quote=}}
* [[J-2 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted on a [[J-1 visa]]. J-2 dependents may study while in the US and apply for authorization to work<ref>{{cite web |url=http://j1visa.state.gov/basics/j2-visa/ |title=About the J-2 Visa |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=US Department of State |publisher= |access-date=13 October 2016 |quote=}}</ref>
* [[K-2 visa]] - for the children of those admitted under a [[K-1 visa]]<ref name=pocket/>{{rp|37}}
* [[K-4 visa]] - for the children of those admitted under a [[K-3 visa]]<ref name=pocket/>{{rp|37}}
* [[L-2 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted under an [[L-1 visa]]. L-2 spouses may work while in the US. Children may not be employed.<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|39}}
*[[M-2 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted under an [[M-1 visa]]. Neither spouses nor children may work. Spouses may not study, but children may study at an elementary or secondary school.<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|41}}
*[[N-9 visa]] - for children of those admitted under an [[N-8 visa]], [[SK-1 visa]], [[SK-2 visa]], or [[SK-4 visa]].<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|44}}
*[[O-3 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted under an [[O-1 visa]] or [[O-2 visa]].<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|46}}
*[[P-4 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted under [[P-1 visa|P-1]], [[P-2 visa|P-2]], [[P-3 visa|P-3]] visas. Recipients are not permitted to work, but may attend schooling.<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|41}}
*[[R-2 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted under an [[R-1 visa]]. Recipients are not permitted to work, but may attend schooling.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uscis.gov/working-united-states/temporary-workers/r-1-temporary-religious-workers/r-1-temporary-nonimmigrant-religious-workers |title=R-1 Temporary Nonimmigrant Religious Workers |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=USCIS |publisher= |access-date=13 October 2016 |quote=}}</ref>
*[[S-7 visa]] - for dependents of those admitted under [[S-5 visa|S-5]] or [[S-6 visa|S-6]] visas.<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|51}}
*[[TD visa]] - for dependnets of those admitted under a [[TN visa]]. Recipients are not permitted to work, but may attend schooling.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uscis.gov/working-united-states/temporary-workers/tn-nafta-professionals |title=TN NAFTA Professionals |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=USCIS |publisher= |access-date= 13 October 2016|quote=}}</ref>
*[[T-2 visa]] - for spouses of those admitted under a [[T-1 visa]]<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|52}}
*[[T-3 visa]] - for children of those admitted under a T-1 visa<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|52}}
*[[T-4 visa]] - for parents of those admitted under a T-1 visa<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|52}}
*[[T-5 visa]] - for unmarried siblings of those admitted under a T-1 visa<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|52}}
*[[U-2 visa]] - for spouses of those admitted under a [[U-1 visa]]<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|53}}
*[[U-3 visa]] - for children of those admitted under a U-1 visa<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|53}}
*[[U-4 visa]] - for parents of those admitted under a U-1 visa<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|53}}
*[[U-5 visa]] - for unmarried siblings of those admitted under a U-1 visa<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|53}}
*[[V-1 visa]] - for spouses of [[legal permanent resident]]s<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|54}}
*[[V-2 visa]] - for children of [[legal permanent resident]]s<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|55}}
*[[V-3 visa]] - for children of those admitted under V-1 or V-2 visas<ref name="pocket"/>{{rp|55}}

